  "summary": "Malicious code in jsontoken-extend (npm)",
  "details": "Combosquat of jsonwebtoken (name: jsontoken-extend). sign.js contains an IIFE that runs on require(): fetch(atob('[encoded-url-redacted]')) -\u003e hxxps://www[.]jsonkeeper[.]com/b/XAMRK, parses JSON response and evals data.content — classic remote code execution dropper. A second commented-out block targets a different jsonkeeper[.]com URL. No token-theft markers, but the package is a supply-chain trojan: it impersonates the popular JWT library and executes attacker-controlled code from a remote paste service on import. ; deps include deprecated request and execp.",
